    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Functions\n",
        "\n",
        "A function is a reusable block of code. You define it once and call it as many times as you like.  The syntax is very simple:"
      ],
      "id": "e1dbbefb"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "def greet(name):\n",
        "    print(f\"Hello, {name}!\")\n",
        "\n",
        "greet(\"Alice\")\n",
        "greet(\"Bob\")"
      ],
      "id": "cce74f8a",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "Functions can send a value back using **return**:"
      ],
      "id": "137959a9"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "def add(a, b):\n",
        "    return a + b\n",
        "\n",
        "result = add(3, 7)\n",
        "print(result)  # 10"
      ],
      "id": "cc8097f2",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "You can set default values for parameters:"
      ],
      "id": "9f70ab4c"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "def greet(name, greeting=\"Hello\"):\n",
        "    print(f\"{greeting}, {name}!\")\n",
        "\n",
        "greet(\"Alice\")              # Uses default: \"Hello, Alice!\"\n",
        "greet(\"Bob\", \"Good morning\")  # Overrides default"
      ],
      "id": "a2c411c9",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
